f=Engineering/ops/custom/release-discipline/SKILL.md · in=release-discipline ops's shipping law: **no deploy without tested rollback.** release enters production through fixed checklist quinn's GATE PASS hand, rollback path exercised *before* deploy, deploy executed strategy playbook prescribes, health verified after, clean abort path step. rollback tested first because rollback never run hope, path. · p=operator's stated goal "maintain everything without breaking stuff" production breakage becomes real. production disasters aren't bad code; they're bad *shipping*: rollback, health check, migration run mid-deploy agent, Friday-evening push nobody watched. skill makes shipping boring, reversible, observed. · wu=Triggers: "deploy," "ship it," "release production," "rollback," "canary," "is safe deploy," post-GATE-PASS handoff quinn, any hotfix (which follows discipline, faster never different one). · st:/ Protocol=`Release candidate arrives \· -> PRECONDITIONS: quinn GATE PASS (quality) + no open rail violation (security) — both, always \· -> ROLLBACK FIRST: identify the rollback path (previous artifact / migration down-script / \· flag-off) and EXERCISE it in staging — a documented-but-untested rollback fails this step \· -> Rail 3 check: any DB migration in this release → dana's prepared script, OPERATOR runs it,` · in=**Both verdicts, exceptions.** quinn's GATE PASS clean charter state preconditions deploy external tool call sequence, runs under locked plan (Rail like everything else. deploy plan lists steps; off-plan action mid-deploy halts. **Exercise rollback before deploying.** staging: roll previous version back in, confirm serves, confirm data compatibility (schema N-1 tolerance expand-contract). Record evidence checklist. "We rollback script" without run FAIL. **Migrations sequenced, operator-run.** Expand-migrate-contract: additive schema changes ship first (operator runs dana's script), code tolerates schemas deploys, contraction comes later deploy stays independently rollback-able. agent-executed destructive migration Rail breach, top severity. **Pick strategy risk, playbook.** Blue-green swap-and-verify, canary gradual user-facing risk, rolling stateless routine (patterns credited marketplace; business's actual mechanics live platform-playbook). choice recorded checklist, improvised. **Verify, watch.** Health endpoints, error rates latency against maintenance-hygiene's baselines, smoke operator's critical flows. hold watch window (`deploy_watch_window`, config) before calling done regressions surface first window, first minute. **Roll back first, diagnose second.** verification fails, restoring service beats understanding failure. Roll back, open incident-response users affected; post-mortem finds why. **Hotfixes follow discipline.** matrix's hotfix row (quinn) covers reduced pre-ship tiers; nothing reduces rollback requirement verify steps. Speed comes checklist short, skipping it. · of=`## Deploy Record: [release] — [date] \· Preconditions: quinn GATE PASS [ref] \· charter clean ✓ \· locked plan [plan id] \· Rollback: path [artifact/script/flag] \· exercised in staging ✓ [evidence] \· Migrations: [none / dana script ref → operator-run ✓, sequenced] \· Strategy: [blue-green/canary/rolling] per [playbook §] \· Deployed: [time]` · pr=**No deploy without tested rollback** untested rollback rollback., **Both gates precede ship** quality (quinn) security (charter), independently., **Deploys run under locked plans** off-plan step mid-deploy halts, any agent., **Migrations operator-run sequenced** expand-migrate-contract; deploys never auto-run destructive changes (Rail 3)., **Roll back first, diagnose second** service restoration outranks root-causing moment., **Hotfix checklist, faster** never different discipline. · f=staging environment rollback exercised against production-shaped local/ephemeral environment, labeled such; gap flagged operator infrastructure debt., Rollback genuinely impossible change (rare: irreversible data transform) change requires explicit operator sign-off *before* deploy, written recovery plan place rollback, tech-debt/risk entry never silent exception., playbook business's host deploy manually checklist, method-only, start playbook what learned (platform-playbooks sibling). · b:with Other Skills=**quinn/test-strategy** decides *whether* ships (GATE PASS); skill decides *how* ships safely., **incident-response** (sibling) takes over deploy (or anything else) hurts users; skill's rollback often first action., **maintenance-hygiene** (sibling) owns monitoring baselines skill verifies against., **platform-playbooks** (sibling) holds dated, host-specific mechanics (commands, consoles, pipelines) skill invariant discipline over them., **dev/delivery-governance**: "rollback-ready" definition done skill's requirement surfacing upstream., **dana** (when built) authors migration scripts; operator executes them (Rail 3).